uuppddaattee -- System Administration

Update file systems periodically
/eettcc/uuppddaattee

uuppddaattee periodically  calls ssyynncc to write  to the disk all  file system data
that are in memory.  It never exits.

The initialization command file /eettcc/rrcc normally executes uuppddaattee. It should
not be executed directly.

